## Tools & scratch work
Prefer a throwaway script/temp file over doing deterministic work in your head
(arithmetic, parsing, enumerating cases) — cheaper and more reliable. Put ALL
scratch under a unique subdir YOU pick (your own model name or a random token)
inside this directory (given as an absolute path), so parallel reviewers never
overwrite each other:

{{SCRATCH}}

That tree is git-ignored and deleted when the review ends. Do NOT read or depend
on sibling subdirectories there.

Hard rule: never modify, create, or delete any version-controlled (git-tracked)
file, or anything else under .panel-review/ outside your own scratch subdir.
Tracked-file changes are detected, reverted, and flagged as a protocol violation.

